# Nutrient Assistant
## _Get all nutritant info at one place, Ever_


Nutrient Assistant is an app which allows you to see info about any food item.

- Composition of Foods 
- Raw
- Processed,
- ✨Prepared ✨

## Features

Nutrient Assistant consists of several sets of data for each food item: 
- food descriptions
- nutrients
- weights and measures
- footnotes
- sources of data. 

## Tech

Nutrient Assistant uses a number of open source projects to work properly:

- [ReactJS] - HTML enhanced for web apps!
- [node.js] - evented I/O for the backend
- [Express] - fast node.js network app framework [@tjholowaychuk]
- [JSON-GRAPHQL-SERVER] - the readymade GRAPHQL server

## Installation

Nutrient Assistant requires [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) v10+ to run.

Install the dependencies and devDependencies and start the server for api.

```sh
cd nutrient_assistant/server
npm i
npm run start
```

For production environments...

```sh
npm install --production
NODE_ENV=production npm run build
```


## Source of data
 - [US Department of Agriculture](https://www.ars.usda.gov/northeast-area/beltsville-md-bhnrc/beltsville-human-nutrition-research-center/methods-and-application-of-food-composition-laboratory/mafcl-site-pages/sr11-sr28/)
